President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. D. Brent Hardt is nominated for Ambassador to the Co-operative Republic of Guyana, Donald W. Koran is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Rwanda, and Geeta Pasi is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Djibouti. Additionally, Michael Les Benedict is appointed as a Member of the Permanent Committee for the Oliver Wendell Holmes Devise. D. Brent Hardt is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as Charg√© d'Affaires ad interim at the U.S. Embassy to Barbados and the Eastern Caribbean. Donald W. Koran is the Director for the Office of Africa Analysis in the Bureau of Intelligence and Research at the U.S. Department of State. Geeta Pasi is the Director of East African Affairs in the Africa Bureau at the Department of State. Michael Les Benedict is a leading scholar of American constitutional history and the Civil War and Reconstruction. He is emeritus professor of history at The Ohio State University.